nd third place.</p><p><strong>Juding Criteria</strong></p><ul><li>Desirability - How impactful will the solution be to end-users? What proof points are available to demonstrate that the solution is meaningful for users?</li><li>Feasibility - How feasible is the solution in the context of the built environment, considering existing and future infrastructure and processes?</li><li>Viability - To what extent is the solution a viable option for the challenge?</li><li>Pitch - How well are the challenge and solution articulated by the team? Is the innovation clearly described and easy to understand?</li></ul><br /><br /><h3>Prizes</h3><p>Teams will compete against all other teams in their city for 3 top prizes:</p><p><strong>1st Place</strong>&nbsp;$3,000 USD</p><p><strong>2nd Place</strong>&nbsp;$1,500 USD</p><p><strong>3rd Place</strong>&nbsp;$500 USD</p></div></div></div>','https://www.hackworks.com/uploads/hackathon/giftthecode2018/giftthecode2018-photo-en.jpg?1537389224?v1.18b','giftthecode@hackworks.com','2000','giftthecode.ca','https://www.hackworks.com/uploads/hackathon/giftthecode2018/giftthecode2018-banner-en.jpg?1537389224?v1.18b',''),('8','Google Cloud Sprint Montreal','2020/03/01','Calle inventada','Lugo','España','<p>Oxford Properties is a global real estate owner, investor, developer and property management company. As a group passionate about innovation in construction, architecture and building design, we are inviting 400 of the best minds to gather in 4 cities around the world to develop solutions for some of the most pressing challenges in the sector today.</p><p>Join us in Boston for an unforgettable innovation experience!</p><p><strong>Agenda</strong></p><p><strong>Day 1</strong><br /><strong>8:00AM</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;Registration &amp; Breakfast<br /><strong>9:00AM</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;Kickoff &amp; Opening Remarks<br /><strong>10:00AM</strong>&nbsp;Hacking Begins<br /><strong>12:00PM</strong>&nbsp; Lunch<br /><strong>1:00PM</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; H